# skillsmith — Environment Variables
# Copy to .env and fill in only what you need. The CLI itself requires ZERO secrets.
# These keys are ONLY for the optional agent-native harness layer (.mcp.json MCP servers).

# GitHub PAT — used by the `github` MCP server (and, later, the GitHub-based skill registry).
# Create a fine-grained token at: https://github.com/settings/tokens
# Scopes: repo read/write for publishing skills; public_repo is enough for browsing.
GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN=ghp_...

# That's it. context7, memory, and obsidian MCP servers (see .mcp.json) need no keys —
# memory reads ./memory/MEMORY.md and obsidian reads ./brain locally.
